                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-15T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1918—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6282. Chinese Minister has informed the Department that his Government has
                    already communicated to the French Government its request that it be represented
                    on the Supreme War Council whenever questions involving the Far East and
                    especially China are under discussion. You will take up the matter with the
                    French Government and support the request of China in this respect. Please
                    advise <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel House</persName> of this action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
